JOHANNESBURG – Treasury has lashed out at US-based research firm and short seller, Viceroy over its bruising report on Capitec bank. It says Viceroy was reckless and did not act in the interest of financial stability in South Africa. READ: Capitec rating not impacted by Viceroy report: S&P Global Treasury says it's satisfied with the assurance from the South African Reserve Bank (SARB), that Capitec is well capitalised, liquid, and solvent. It’s moved to assure depositors that their funds are safe. Treasury is also calling on the Financial Services Board (FSB), and the Johannesburg Stock Exchange to consider a market abuse investigation into Viceroy. eNCA